This paper deals with transmission over a binary channel using a low-density parity check code, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the posterior measure over the code bits, which is a concept in network information theory (cs.NI). The analysis of the correlation between code bits is related to statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses graph theory to analyze the decay of correlations, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
